<A NAME="phi(double, int)"><!-- --></A><H3>
phi</H3>
<PRE>
public static double[] <B>phi</B>(double&nbsp;x,
                           int&nbsp;k)</PRE>
<DL>
<DD>Evaluate the shifted normalized Legendre polynomials up to the
       given order at x defined on [0,1].

       These are also our scaling functions, phi_i(x) , i=0..k-1

       In addition to forming an orthonormal basis on [0,1] we have
       phi_j(1/2-x) = (-1)^j phi_j(1/2+x)

       (the wavelets are similar with phase (-1)^(j+k)).
<P>
<DD><DL>
<DT><B>Parameters:</B><DD><CODE>x</CODE> - point at which to evaluate polynomials<DD><CODE>k</CODE> - evaluate first k polynomials
<DT><B>Returns:</B><DD>double[] first k polynomials evaluated at point x</DL>
</DD>
</DL>
<HR>

